folder: Crosby Street & Prince Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Crosby Street, adjoining the N. W. corner of Prince Street, showing Niblo's Garden Theatre as it appeared April 14, 1895. Enclosing this site in the form of an ell, is the Metropolitan Hotel. This structure faces on Broadway and Prince Street. It will be replaced with the present Havemeyer Bldg.

April 14, 1895

E. D. Bellows, photo
Gift of Urbrock Collection

folder: Prince Street & Crosby Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Prince Street, north side, east from but not including Crosby, to Lafayette Streets; also shown is Lafayette Street, at and adjoining N.W. corner of Prince Street. No. 63 Prince Street, at the corner was the home of Samuel Gouveneur when his father-in-law, ex-president James Monroe died here in 1831.

About 1915.

Gift of Samuel Landsman.

text:
Prince Street, north side, east from and including Crosby, to Lafayette (Elm) Streets. Also shown is Lafayette (Elm) Street, at, and adjoining the N.W. corner of Prince Street. No. 63 Prince Street, at the N.W. corner of Lafayette (Elm) Street, was the home of Samuel Gouverneur when his father-in-law ex-president James Monroe died here in 1831.

About 1917.

Edwin Levick.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.
